    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.1.13",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "13",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.1.13",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "All the persons were four thousand and six hundred - How amazingly were the Jews diminished, that this handful was all who were carried captive!",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 25,
      "token_count": 27
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.1.17",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "17",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.1.17",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "All the days of his life - Here ends the history of the kingdom of Judah. I shall only observe the severe judgment of God upon this people, whose kingdom was made up of the two tribes of Judah and Benjamin, and half the tribe of Manasseh. In the numbering of the persons belonging to these two tribes, Numb 1:27 ,35,37, (counting half of the number of the tribe of Manasseh) we find one hundred twenty - six thousand one hundred: Numb 26:22 ,34,41, we find of them one hundred forty - eight thousand four hundred and fifty. Here, ver. 52:30 , we find no more of them carried into captivity, than four thousand and six hundred. From whence we may judge what a multitude of them were slain by the sword, by the famine, and pestilence! It is a dreadful thing to fall into the hands of the living God, to mock his messengers, despise his words, and misuse his prophets, 'till there be no remedy, 2Chron 36:16 .",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [
        "Num.1.27",
        "Num.26.22",
        "2Chr.36.16"
      ],
      "word_count": 170,
      "token_count": 228
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.1.19",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "19",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.1.19",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Weary - With that weight of judgment which shall be upon them. The words - The prophetical words of Jeremiah; for the matter of the next chapter is historical, and the book of Lamentations is not prophetical.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 37,
      "token_count": 46
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.1.20",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "20",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.1.20",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "A widow - She that had a king, or rather a God, that was an husband to her, now was forsaken of God, and her king taken from her.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 29,
      "token_count": 35
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.1.22",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "22",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.1.22",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Because - Because of the servitude and oppression exercised among them: oppression by their rulers, and servitude more generally; keeping their servants beyond the year of jubilee, when they ought to be set at liberty. The straits - Those that pursued them overtook them in places where they could not escape.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 51,
      "token_count": 62
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.6",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "6",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.6",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Pleasant things - Has laid violent hands on them. The things of the sanctuary were always pleasant things to those that feared God.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 23,
      "token_count": 27
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.7",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "7",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.7",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Bread - Even in a land that ordinarily flowed with milk and honey, they were at a loss for bread to eat. Given - And gave any thing for something to satisfy their hunger. Vile - Miserable or contemptible.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 39,
      "token_count": 48
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.8",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "8",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.8",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Is it nothing - The prophet speaks in the name of the Jewish church.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 14,
      "token_count": 15
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.9",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "9",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.9",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Fire - A judgment as consuming, and afflictive as fire.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 10,
      "token_count": 13
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.10",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "10",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.10",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Is bound - Put upon my neck on account of my transgressions. Wreathed - My punishments are twisted as cords; I have a complication of judgments upon me, sword, famine, pestilence, captivity.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 32,
      "token_count": 45
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.11",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "11",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.11",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "An assembly - God had called an assembly of Chaldeans against the city, to crush the inhabitants of it. Trodden - God had trodden upon the Jews as men use to stamp grapes in a wine - press.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 38,
      "token_count": 46
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.12",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "12",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.12",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The comforter - God.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 4,
      "token_count": 6
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.13",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "13",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.13",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Jerusalem - Is become loathsome and filthy.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 7,
      "token_count": 11
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.15",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "15",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.15",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Deceived - They did not answer my expectation.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 8,
      "token_count": 10
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.16",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "16",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.16",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Death - By famine and pestilence.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 6,
      "token_count": 9
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.17",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "17",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.17",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "They - The neighbouring nations. Like me - But thou hast foretold their destruction also, and hast by me proclaimed it: and thou shalt in that day bring them into as sad a condition as I am in now.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 39,
      "token_count": 45
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.20",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "20",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.20",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "His footstool - His temple; but suffered the Chaldeans to destroy it. Cast down - That is, thrown them down from the highest glory and honour, to the meanest degree of servitude.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 32,
      "token_count": 44
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.21",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "21",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.21",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Polluted - Dealt with them as with a polluted thing; cast them off, brake them in pieces.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 17,
      "token_count": 22
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.2.22",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "22",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.2.22",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The horn - All their beauty and strength. Drawn back - God hath drawn back his assistance which he was wont to give the Jews against their enemies. Round about - God consumed them, not in this or that part, but round about, as a fire seizing an house at once on all sides.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 54,
      "token_count": 61
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.2",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "2",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.2",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "His tabernacle - His temple. The places - The synagogues. The king - By the king and the priests are meant persons of greatest rank and eminency, though it is thought here is a special reference to Zedekiah the king of Judah, and Seraiah who was the high priest; the former of which was miserably handled, the latter slain.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 59,
      "token_count": 79
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.3",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "3",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.3",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "They - The enemies with their triumphs and blasphemies, made as great a noise, as those that sang holy songs, or played on instruments, were wont to make to the glory of God.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 33,
      "token_count": 40
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.4",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "4",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.4",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The wall - The strength and security of the Jews. A line - Artificers used with lines not only to mark out places for building, but also for destruction, to direct them what to cut off; and such a line is here meant.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 43,
      "token_count": 50
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.5",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "5",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.5",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Among the Gentiles - In miserable captivity. The law - Is no more read, opened or observed. Her prophets - They had but very few prophets, from this time to the time of the gospel, and very few of those at this time alive had any revelation from God.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 49,
      "token_count": 56
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.6",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "6",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.6",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The virgins - The whole city is in a mournful posture.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 11,
      "token_count": 15
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.7",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "7",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.7",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Mine eyes - This whole verse is but expressive of the prophets great affliction for the miseries come upon the Jews. He wept himself almost blind. Bowels - His passion had disturbed his bodily humours, that his bowels were troubled. Liver - His gall lying under his liver. All these are expressions of great affliction and sorrow. Swoon - During the famine, occasioned by the long siege.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 67,
      "token_count": 85
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.8",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "8",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.8",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Bosom - When they died in their mother's arms.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 9,
      "token_count": 13
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.9",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "9",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.9",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Who - There was no people whose condition was in any degree parallel to the misery of the Jews: nor was there any cure for them, their breach was like a sea breach where the waters come in with such a torrent, that there is no making any defence against them.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 51,
      "token_count": 55
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.10",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "10",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.10",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The prophets - False prophets told you vain stories. Not discovered - Whereas they ought to have made you sensible of your sins, and this might have prevented your captivity. False burdens - False stories to encourage you in sin, and so cause your banishment.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 45,
      "token_count": 51
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.14",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "14",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.14",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "O wall - That is, those that are upon it.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 10,
      "token_count": 12
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.16",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "16",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.16",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Whom - Not the Heathen, but to thy own people. Women - Wilt thou suffer women to satisfy their hunger with the fruit of their own bodies?",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 27,
      "token_count": 33
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.18",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "18",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.18",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "My terrors - As my people were wont to be called together from all parts in a solemn day, so now my terrible enemies, or terrible things are by thee called together.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 32,
      "token_count": 36
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.20",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "20",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.20",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "I am the man - It seems, this is spoken in the name of the people, who were before set out under the notion of a woman.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 27,
      "token_count": 30
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.23",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "23",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.23",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Made old - All my beauty is gone, and all my strength.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 12,
      "token_count": 14
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.24",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "24",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.24",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Builded - He hath built forts and batteries against my walls and houses.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 13,
      "token_count": 15
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Lam.3.28",
      "book": "Lamentations",
      "book_osis": "Lam",
      "book_number": 25,
      "chapter": 3,
      "verse_range": "28",
      "verse_range_osis": "Lam.3.28",
      "verse_text": null,
